Kenya received $1.9 billion in
remittances over the past 12 months, according to a report by
Bendixen and Amandi commissioned by the World Bank. About 14
percent of Kenyaâ€™s adult population regularly receive money from
about, with an average payment of $105 seven times a year.  Bendixen and Amandi surveyed 2,423 people between July 14
and Sept. 4, according to the report handed to journalists in
the capital, Nairobi, today. The survey had a margin of error of
